
A. Nilagang Baka ala Bulalo

Prep time:  5 mins
Cook time:  3 hours
Total time: 3 hours 5 mins

Recipe type: Beef
Cuisine: Filipino
Serves: 4

Ingredients:
* 1½ lb. beef chuck, cubed
* 1 tablespoon whole peppercorn
* 2 medium yellow onions, wedged
* 8 cups water
* 1 sweet corn, divided into 4 pieces
* 4 to 4 tablespoons fish sauce
* 1 beef cube
* 1 large baking potato, cubed
* ½ head small cabbage, sliced

Instructions:
1. Pour water into a cooking pot. Let boil.
2. Add whole peppercorn and onion. Boil for 5 minutes.
3. Add beef chuck. Let the water re-boil and then cover the cooking pot. Continue to boil in medium heat for 2 hours.
4. Add corn and then cover the pot. Cook for 1 hour.
5. Add beef cube and potato. Cook for 5 to 6 minutes.
6. Pour fish sauce into the pot. Stir.
7. Add cabbage. Cover the pot. Cook for 5 minutes.
8. Transfer to a serving bowl.
9. Serve hot. Share and enjoy!

B. Paksiw na Lechon Kawali

Prep time:  5 mins
Cook time:  55 mins
Total time: 1 hour

Recipe type: Pork
Cuisine: Filipino
Serves: 4

Ingredients

* 1½ lb. lechon kawaii, sliced
* 1½ cups lechon sauce
* 2½ cups beef broth
* 3 cloves garlic, minced
* 2 medium onion, diced
* ½ cup granulated white sugar
* 1 teaspoon whole peppercorn
* 6 pieces dried bay leaves
* 2 tablespoons soy sauce
* ¼ cup white vinegar
* 3 tablespoons cooking oil
* Salt to taste

Instructions

1. Heat oil in a cooking pot.
2. Saute garlic and onion.
3. Once the onion gets soft, add the lechon kawaii. Saute for 3 minutes.
4. Add soy sauce and beef broth. Let boil.
5. Add whole peppercorn and dried bay leaves. Cover the pot and cook in medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
6. Pour vinegar into the pot. Let the liquid re-boil.
7. Add lechon sauce. Stir. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
8. Add sugar and salt. Continue to cook until the liquid reduces to half.
9. Transfer to a serving bowl. Serve.
10. Share and enjoy!

C. Pancit Sotanghon Na May Hipon

Prep time:  5 mins
Cook time:  18 mins
Total time: 23 mins

Recipe type: Noodles
Cuisine: Filipino
Serves: 3

Ingredients:

* 5 ounces Sotanghon noodles
* 1 Knorr Shrimp Cube
* 12 pieces shrimp
* 1 piece Chinese sausage, minced
* 5 cloves garlic, crushed
* 2 cups chopped cabbage
* ¼ cup minced parsley
* ¾ cup carrot, julienne
* ¼ cup chopped scallions
* 2½ tablespoons fish sauce
* 1 small yellow onion, sliced
* 1 tablespoon paprika
* ¼ teaspoon ground black pepper
* 1½ cups water
* 3 tablespoons cooking oil

Instructions:

1. Soak noodles in water for 5 minutes or until it starts to get softer and manageable. Drain the water. Set the noodles aside. Note: Make sure to not soak the noodles longer than 8 minutes.
2. Heat oil in a pot. Sauté garlic until light brown
3. Add onion. Sauté until soft
4. Put the Chinese sausage, parsley, and paprika. Sauté for 30 seconds to 1 minute.
5. Pour-in water and fish sauce. Let boil.
6. Add Knorr Shrimp Cube. Stir. Cover the pot and continue to cook for 5 minutes.
7. Put ground black pepper, shrimp, carrot and cabbage into the pot. Stir and cook for 3 minutes.
8. Add sotanghon and gently stir. Let the noodles absorb the liquid. Cover the pot and continue to cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed fully.
9. Add scallions and toss the noodles.
10. Transfer to a serving plate. Serve!
11. Share and enjoy!


____________________________________________________  MARAH'S RECIPES _________________________________________________________________
I. FRESH STRAWBERRY SHORTCAKE
  (12 Servings)
  Ingredients:
    4 Cups Packages Biscuit Mix
    1 1/2 Cups Sweet Cream
    1 1/2 Tablespoon Sugar
    2 Quarts Strawberry Ice Cream
    2 Quarts Strawberries, Sliced and Sugared
    3 cups Whipped Cream
    1 Cup Chopped Pistachio Nuts
    12 Whole Strawberries

  Instructions:
    Mix packaged Biscuit Mix with cream and sugar until you have a soft dough.
    Beat vigorously until dough is smooth but soft enough to knead.
    Knead lightly on a floured board until smooth enough to roll.
    Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
    Using a -inch round cookie cutter, cut circles from dough.
    Place one inch apart on an unbuttered baking sheet.
    Bake in 450 deg oven for 10 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
    Split shortcakes and cool completely.
    Just before serving, place layers of strawberry ice cream and some sugared
    strawberries in the middle of each shortcake and cover with upper half.
    Top with more berries, whipped cream, a sprinkling of chopped pistachio nuts
    and finally, top each portion with a whole strawberry.

II. BLUEBERRY ICE CREAM DREAM
  (6 Servings)
  Ingredients:
    1 1/2 Quarts Blueberries
    1 1/4 Cups Sugar
    1 Teaspoon Cinnamon
    10  Slices Buttered Bread
    6 Scoops Vanilla Ice Cream

  Instructions:
    Wash Blueberries.
    Cook blueberries slowly with sugar and cinnamon for 10 minutes.
    Trim Crust from bread.
    Butter an 8-inch square baking dish and in it place a single layer of bread.
    Add a layer of berries.
    Alternate bread and berries until pan is full.
    Ending with berries and their juice.
    Bake in 350 deg oven for 25 minutes.
    Chill, Cut in squares.
    Serve topped with vanilla ice cream.

III. HOT FUDGE SNOWBALL
    (for each serving)
    Ingredients:
       1 large Scoop Vanilla Ice Cream
       1 Cup Shredded Coconut
       1/2 cup Hot Fudge Sauce

    Instructions:
      Shape ice cream with a scoop and roll in shredded coconut until well
      coated on all sides. Set on sheet of waxed paper and place in freezer to harden.
      Place snowball in a deep dish.
      Pour hot fudge sauce over it and serve.

